from django.conf import settings
from django.shortcuts import redirect
from urllib.parse import urlencode
from django.http import JsonResponse, request, response

import requests
import json
import datetime


def form_errors(*args):
    """
    Handles form error that are passed back to AJAX calls
    """
    message = ""
    for f in args:
        if f.errors:
            message = f.errors.as_text()
    return message


def recaptcha_validation(token):
    """recaptcha validation"""
    result = requests.post(
        'https://www.google.com/recaptcha/api/siteverify',
        data={
            'secret': settings.RECAPTCHA_PRIVATE_KEY,
            'response': token
        }
    )
    return result.json()


class AjaxFormMixin(object):
    """
    Mixin to ajaxify django form - can be over written in view by calling form_valid method
    """

    def form_invalid(self, form):
        response = super(AjaxFormMixin, self).form_invalid(form)
        if self.request.is_ajax():
            message = form_errors(form)
            return JsonResponse({'result': 'Error', 'message': message})
        return response

    def form_valid(self, form):
        response = super(AjaxFormMixin, self).form_valid(form)
        if self.request.is_ajax():
            form.save()
            return JsonResponse({
                'result': 'Success',
                'message': ''
            })
        return response

fields.title: Darisset Blog with Django
fields.abstract:
This project is named Darisset, so if you are using this Project to create your own project, you will need a little extra configuration. As:
1. Darisset.site folder (your top project container)
2. Darisset_site/darisset folder (your project name)
3. Virtual environment name: env (name whatever you want)
4. Create in the virtual environment an .env file
5. You must change from set.settings.development to your projectname.settings.development.
6. The same work for the test env
fields.content: With this code, you can create complex Django-based websites. very fast, just a few steps! Some of the Django Darisset Blog CMS functionality are: 1. Different virtual environments for development, testing and production 2. Internationalization and localization to support multiple languages 3. Project structure 4. HTML5 Boiler Plate 5. Legacy templates 6. robots.txt and human.txt can be configured 7. Organized sitemap.txt 8. SEO 9. Responsive web design 10. already using Boostrap 4 11. Embed youtube and much more In addition, you can learn how to create this CMS concept step by step manually due to structured code writing.
